cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.BIO, cs.CV, cs.AI

The paper proposes a deep learning model for heart rate variability analysis, which involves both neural network and biological neuron models. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper involves biomedical signal processing and analysis, which suggests cs.BIO (Bioinformatics) as another possible category. The paper also uses ECG data, which involves image processing, and hence cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) could be another relevant category. Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning for classification, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category.
